\cf3\b\fs24 Schwaa's Rant:\cf0\b0\fs20\par
\cf4\b\fs22  This mission might possibly be expanded at some point, or worked into a small campaign, but for now enjoy as is.\par
As corny as it is, I chose TTLG as the title. Now this was not my original title or intention, but I did decide to\par
 dedicate this mission to Through the Looking Glass Studios (as thanks for a great game that is sucking\par
 away all of my time, life and talent -does that sound bad?), and alternately to TTLG.com forums and the Taffers\par
 who have helped and inspired me thru the years. It just seemed to fit so well too, I had to do it.\par
\cf1\f2\fs20 =============================================================================================\par
\cf3\f4\fs28 Intro:\cf4\par
 \cf1\fs22 Rumors around town have it that a cult up on the hill has found a way to extract diamonds from the sky.\par
Sounds fishy, smells fishy too. But it surely isn't the strangest thing I've heard, anyway as sceptical\par
 as I am I've decided to investigate this rumor for myself. What's the worst thing that could happen,\par
 I find some regular old diamonds?\cf4  \par
\cf1\f2\fs20 =============================================================================================\par
\fs28 Important gameplay info:\fs20\par
 I used a few custom scripts. Some objects can only be used/frobbed/read when an item on top of them is moved first.\par
 Dials use a custom script, to use press your mouse key (frob) and hold the button down.\par
 Shadows: I used renderer:runtime object shadows on alot of objects like rocks and trees. If something is between you\par
   and a light it probably casts a shadow (unless you can still see the light-like a small crate, no way you could actually\par
   hide behind one anyway.\par
 Bugs: There are some objects (by who, not sure) in circulation that have nice textures, unfortunately they use the same\par
           model names as the originals, but happen to be rotated 90 degrees. A wood table is one of them, be sure to play\par
           with a clean T2 folder to avoid these problems.\par
